verbose_text: New technologies and advancements have informed us how maternal diet, maternal body composition, and the maternal response to placental hormones and growth factors, in the context of the mother 's own metagenomics and metagenomics of her microbiome, can influence her IR and inflammatory state, beta-cell responses, and the levels of glucose, amino acids, and lipids she exposes to the fetal-placental unit (XREF_FIG).
